25/04/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- The next session of the Turkey-EU Association Council will take place in Luxembourg on Tuesday (26 April). Discussions will focus on Turkey-EU political dialogue, Cyprus re-unification talks and Turkey's commitment to seal an enlarged customs union accord that includes Cyprus.
On Monday, meanwhile, officials from Turkey, Australia, New Zealand, France and India gathered at Gallipoli. They marked the 90th anniversary of one of the most memorable battles of World War I. (TurkishPress.com, AAP - 25/04/05; AP - 23/04/05) 
